@SpartacusX -- No you can't use Venser that way. You can cast Venser if you have Leyline of Anticipation and enough mana on the field but you can't use his abilities. His abilities aren't cards.  

@Wraique --- No. Ball Lightning and Putrefax will still die. Venser puts them into play at the beginning of the End Step. Which means as soon as the Clean Up Phase arrives(which is after the End Step begins) Ball Lightning, Putrefax, and any other card that gets sacrificed at end of turn still goes bye bye. (Read the rulings they simplify it better than I do).  

When a card states "the next end step" that means the VERY next End Step. Which is the end of the turn it happened.  

@BloodDragon --- Yes. If a card states "When ~~!~~ enters the battlefield" or "when ~~!~~ leaves the battlefield" those abilities will trigger, unless another spell or ability(even it's own) prevents it from happening.  

This card gets a 5/5 stars from me.
